.TH "mesh_nexthop_lookup_nolearn" 9 "mesh_nexthop_lookup_nolearn" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mesh_nexthop_lookup_nolearn \- try to set next hop without path discovery
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mesh_nexthop_lookup_nolearn
.BI "(struct ieee80211_sub_if_data *sdata "  ","
.BI "struct sk_buff *skb "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdata" 12
network subif the frame will be sent through
.IP "skb" 12
802.11 frame to be sent
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Check if the meshDA (addr3) of a unicast frame is a direct neighbor.
And if so, set the RA (addr1) to it to transmit to this node directly,
avoiding PREQ/PREP path discovery.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if the next hop was found and -ENOENT otherwise.
